Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with 1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, heat a large saucepan with a tight-fitting lid on medium-high heat. Add the @Slow Cooked British Chicken{290%grams} along with the juices from the packet.

Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a #fork{}, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the chicken is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}(halved lengthways and thinly sliced).

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Mix in the tomato chunks. Set aside.

Once tender, remove the lid from the pan and shred the chicken.

Stir through the @Hot Sauce{30%grams}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Butter{20%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, toss the lettuce with the tomato chunks and dressing until evenly coated.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}. Top with the shredded chicken and sprinkle over the cheese.

Add the salad to one side and drizzle the @Burger Sauce{30%grams} on top.

Sprinkle with the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!

